                <td bgColor="#ECECEC"><textarea cols="48" name="Message" rows="12" wrap="VIRTUAL" onselect="storeCaret(this);" onclick="storeCaret(this);" onkeyup="storeCaret(this);" onchange="storeCaret(this);">[quote][i]Originally posted by Druid02[/i]
[br][quote]your saying since it is illegal it shouldn't be done...so you can't really say one is ok and the other isn't.[/quote]

Wrong.  I'm saying it shouldn't be done because it is stealing.  Because it directly rips off somebody else.

If you're trying to find a song, and you're not sure who the artist is, you're not ripping anyone off.  You're trying to find out what artist's CD you want to buy.  But once you download the song you want, and keep it to take the place of actually owning it, you've crossed the line into stealing.

Speeding in your car is illegal, but there's a big difference between five over and thirty-five over.  Thus I see a distinction.
[/quote]</textarea><br /></td>
